Types of vitamins and their roles:

1. Vitamin A (Retinol)
- Role: Supports healthy vision, immune function, bone growth, cell division and differentiation, and skin health.
- Sources: Liver, fish liver oils, egg yolks, dairy products, orange and yellow vegetables like carrots and sweet potatoes.

2. B-vitamins
a) Thiamine (B1)
- Role: Helps with energy metabolism; nerve function & brain development
- Source: Whole grains, legumes

b) Riboflavin (B2)
- Role: Antioxidant that helps protect cells from damage; assists in converting food into energy
- Source: Dairy products,

c) Niacin (B3)
- Role : Necessary for the conversion of food to energy; maintaining nervous system functions 
 -Sources : Chicken,turkey meat,certain types of fish like tuna 

d) Pantothenic Acid(B5):
    Roles ; Supports nerves,muscles functions  serotonin production 
     source ;Organ meet,fish,brown rice , milk 
     
e )Vitamin B6(Pyridoxine ):
        role ; creating new red blood cells,making hemoglobin source   pork poultry ,whole cerals,potatoes  

 f)Vitamin B7(Biotin):	
            Roles-supports metabolism,blood glucose regulation reproduction  	
                sources-almonds,nuts egg yolk
